{{Quote|Mother of Kwath&hellip;There must be enough rhydonium in here to blow up the entire Republic fleet.|Meebur Gascon, upon seeing rhydonium in a ''Venator''-class Star Destroyer|<ref name="PONR">{{TCW|Point of No Return (The Clone Wars)}}</ref>}}
A '''kurkuoth''', sometimes referred to as a '''kwath''', was a silicon-based life form similar to the [[Mynock/Legends|Mynock]]. They were considered pests, as they fed on energy sources found on [[Starship/Legends|ships]] or in [[Spaceport/Legends|spaceports]].

Kurkuoths were [[Spider/Legends|spider]]-like creatures with a square central body and four segmented legs, one on each corner. The central body, typically less than half a [[Meter/Legends|meter]] long, was protected by a hard shell that was jointed to allow the creature to fold itself nearly in half, giving it access to small openings. A [[Mouth/Legends|mouth]] was on the lower part of the shell with clusters of [[Eye/Legends|eyes]] on both the top and bottom of the central body, allowing the kurkuoth to see any signs of danger while feeding.

Kurkuoths were cowardly, usually choosing flight over fight. However, a kwath that had developed a nest and a [[Foodstuff/Legends|food]] source for its [[Youngling/Legends|offspring]] would often be far braver. They [[Reproduction/Legends|reproduced]] asexually, with environmental conditions affecting the number of [[Egg/Legends|eggs]] the [[Parent/Legends|parent]] generated. A typical kurkuoth lifespan was one to three [[Standard year/Legends|years]].

Kwath could be used as an expletive. During the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]], [[D-Squad/Legends|D-Squad]] docked in a [[Venator-class Star Destroyer/Legends|''Venator''-class Star Destroyer]] and quickly discovered that it had been hijacked by [[Confederacy of Independent Systems/Legends|Separatist]] [[Droid/Legends|droids]]. They then found that the docking bays were filled with [[Rhydonium/Legends|rhydonium]],<ref name="PONR" /> which was known to be explosive.<ref name="Missing in Action">{{TCW|Missing in Action}}</ref> [[Meebur Gascon/Legends|Meebur Gascon]], the leader of the group, was very surprised by the large amount of rhydonium and uttered the phrase "Mother of Kwath."<ref name="PONR" />

